Welcome to the setup program for CS-Project, version <b>{VERSION_STRING}</b>!

<p>
	In this step, we need to determine some basic information about the database.
	The database should NOT exist yet: it will be created later.  
</p>


<form method="POST">
<table border=1 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0>
	<tr>
		<th colspan="3"></th>

	</tr>
	<tr>
		<th>Database Name (cs_project)</th>
		
		<td><input type="text" name="fields[db_name]" value="{db_name}"></td>
		
		<td>Name of the database within PostgreSQL (i.e. "cs_project")</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>

		<th>Hostname (localhost)</th>
		
		<td><input type="text" name="fields[db_host]" value="{db_host}"></td>
		
		<td>Fully qualified host name (like "taz.google.com" or "localhost").</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<th>Port (5432)</th>
		
		<td><input type="text" name="fields[db_port]" value="{db_port}"></td>

		
		<td>Port to connect to PostgreSQL on (default is 5432).</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<th>Database Username (postgres)</th>
		
		<td><input type="text" name="fields[db_user]" value="{db_user}"></td>
		
		<td>Username for connecting to PostgreSQL (if you don't know, it's probably "postgres", though connecting as a SUPERUSER is generally accepted as a BAD THING).</td>
	</tr>

	<tr>
		<th>Database Password</th>
		
		<td><input type="text" name="fields[db_pass]" value="{db_pass}"></td>
		
		<td>Password for connecting to PostgreSQL (for a trusted connection, this can be blank).</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="3" align="center"><input type="submit" value="Go to next step"></td>

	</tr>
</table>
</form>


